+ Fix all issues with PCBs
+ Put my ARM gumstix inside, using GPIO -> i2c bus
+ create USB interface


To self-power from USB, probably need to use 6ma current rather than 12.
SAA-1064 uses approx 150ma at full draw at 5V, times 4 is 600ma which
is more then the 400ma a USB port can provide.

USB interface notes:
  http://home.ict.nl/~fredkrom/pe0fko/g8voi_guide/
  http://www.evilmadscientist.com/article.php/avrtargetboards
  http://www.ladyada.net/make/usbtinyisp/
  http://www.harbaum.org/till/i2c_tiny_usb/index.shtml
  
  Parts:
    2x3 DIP adapter
    8-pin socket
    
    2 3.6V zener diode
    1 12MHz crystal, HC49U package
    1 2.2K resistor
    2 68Ohm resistor
    2 10K resistor
    2 22pF cap
    1 100nF cap
    1 10uF electrolytic
    1 USB-B connector
    1 4-pin i2c connector
    1 Attiny45 DIP 20MHz
    1 8-pin socket
    
    
